&gt; Lamia smiled and said &quot;Great, GREAT !!!&quot;

Marauder nodded as Lamia expressed her agreement. He turned back to
the panel he stood in front of and began to program into it a series
of instructions.

&quot;This should not involve a major alteration of your structure, but I
will be installing several skill sets that should involve your battle
prowess as well as your tactical knowledge.&quot; he turned back to look at
her, &quot;We have had several . . . um . . additions that we can use.&quot;

He smiled as he turned back to the panel. As he worked a door opened
and Dirge walked through and he looked over at Lamia and then at
Marauder. &quot;Sir, the Insectors have their orders and are preparing now
for the next stage in the plan.&quot;

Maurader nodded and then glanced up at Dirge, &quot;Good.&quot; he said as he
straightened. &quot;I have programmed several changes that will be made to
Lamia.&quot; he said gesturing at the female that stood at his side.
&quot;Prepare the reformatting chamber.&quot;

Dirge glanced at Lamia, his face curious and perhaps a bit annoyed. He
was about to day something, but a subtle shake of the head from
Marauder forestalled it. Instead he just turned back to Lamia.

&quot;This way.&quot; Dirge said to Lamia as he gestured to another door that
slid open in the wall. The interior of that room glowed slightly as
energies coursed through it. In the center of the room was a pod that
was laid back like a bed.

Dirge glanced back at Lamia, &quot;Lay here.&quot; he said shortly, gesturing at
the pod bed.

